metadata.description:
For the first time in the history of the world, art can directly have a monetary impact on underserved and unbanked people worldwide. ‚ÄúFlamin-go with Love‚Äù is my first NFT drop in support of Impact Market- a crypto Unconditional Basic Income (UBI) protocol supporting people globally - some who live on under $2 a day. When this NFT is purchased, 50% will be airdropped to the phones of people in the Coroadinho UBI community program in Maranh√£o, Brazil. People can buy food, medicine, and clean water at local businesses that are also onboarded onto the protocol.

The two flamingos coming together to form a heart celebrate and symbolize the power of crypto and blockchain to spread meaningful action worldwide in minutes.

This NFT will also help fund a public art sculpture. The solar-powered LED neon sculpture will live for two weeks in Black Rock City, Nevada, during Burning Man and then be installed in an outdoor space for the public to enjoy. After the event and public installation, one collector will have the chance to purchase the sculpture.

Through the sale of this NFT, 50% will go to Impact Market, and 50% will fund the creation of this sculpture. The sale of the sculpture will also have a split of 50% to the artists and 50% to Impact Market.

Unlockable usable AR files for your phone or your VR space can be found at app.charmverse.io/fiona-aboud/page-8646698307866953

If you purchased 10 or more NFTs please email me fionaaboud@gmail.com for either a print or a shirt.

metadata.name: "The PFP"
metadata.description:
Looks like Drunk Santa gave everyone his first Christmas present of the year. 

Excited I said the word "first" huh? Yes, Drunk Santa is wasted so he's making it rain throughout the year and beyond. Hopefully Stoned Santa shows up soon with this years blackmarket yield. 

People have asked me all the time how to get their PFP featured in my digital paintings. I've only included my collectors PFP in my art until now. Drunk Santa is here to help. I'm opening it up in 2023 and these are the wallets I'll be picking my characters from now on. 

This piece is called "The PFP" and this token will be the first step in getting yourself/pfp in my future digital paintings works until I die. Some of these paintings will be featured in my solo exhibit at the Anaheim Public Library/Muzeo in 2024, a follow up to my first show back in Feb 22', WAGMI. 

I'm classically trained and people assume I press a button like magic. I've always had a chip on my shoulder thinking digital art will be accepted one day. That day has come for us and it's time for art with our PFPs to take our rightful place in the art world. 

Follow along my career or not and until then, see you all when Drunk Santa hands out his second present. 

Oh yeah, this token is burnable (or not) for the next round of unlocks. Choose wisely while sober.

Briefing: UnderAqua is an underwater universe born out of chaos from the mind of Kenny Scharf. This unique one of a kind story of a post nuclear universe is told through NFT‚Äôs and the participation from its collectors, AKA scientists. This concept represents what is possible when a community comes together to accomplish a goal for the greater good.

The Year: 2045

The Place: An abandoned nuclear power plant off the coast of the Pacific.

The Situation: Unforeseen tectonic movements and intensifying ocean waves crashing against the complex have eroded the bordering wall of a nuclear facility ‚Äì and small cracks have begun to spider along with the concrete. Unbeknownst to all, highly toxic ooze has been seeping into the surrounding waters, converging with a century of untended plastic pollution. When scientists at the plant finally discover the leak ‚Äì years after it began ‚Äì they find that the doomed wildlife has been ravaged by hazardous plastics and radiation from the nuclear plant, permanently mutating the fish, with some exhibiting erratic behaviors and unnatural abilities. For example, some fish have become mutated and others have built underwater metropolises. Some fish have grown legs while others have grown wings. Some smoke weed and some take steroids. The impact of the superpowers combined with their newly found free will is something never before seen. Now it is up to us, a massive task force of analysts known as ‚ÄúUnderAqua,‚Äù to study the effects of radiation on the fish. Each of the experts will be granted full access to the plant‚Äôs staff, tools, and the quarantined areas, which are presumed to house infected species of fish.

The Mission: The lead scientist has a hypothesis that although these fish‚Äôs superpowers can be dangerous, if studied correctly, we can find answers to some of humanity‚Äôs biggest threats. So our goal is to study these fish and figure out not only what specific mutation happened, but figure out how we can apply these superpower-like abilities to help the society for the greater good of humanity.

oscillations #15 by desultor
metadata.description:
**Buckle up buckeroos. oscillations by desultor is a spectacular collection of single-mint 1/1 animated NFT artworks. With mesmerizing repetition, each oscillation depicts an implied movement inward or outward around a central point.**

Using a 16-point symmetric canvas, 5 total colors, and mixed pixel brushes, each piece features unique visual constructs. Pieces are numbered chronologically as they were created with a total of 50 different pieces.

_Inspired by ancient cultures, classic SNES RPGs, and modern science fiction, oscillations were created during organic states of flow with fixed artist conditions. The end result is a collection of varied suggestive visuals I hope you dig as much as I did making them!_

Artist: Isaac Wright

metadata.name: I ACTUALLY PAID FOR THIS (edition of 100)
metadata.description:
This is my third NFT. 

As an artist, I think its significant to adapt, change, and allow my thoughts to resonate and be embraced by contemporary culture regardless of medium or image. 

I always have this apprehension towards cryptos, NFTs and virtual works out of my own concern of imminent disaster. Whether it will be an economical, physical, or astronomic, it feels like Crypto is within a space of constant threat and attack from different parts of society, yet it still thrives, grows and breathes under this threat. I find that exciting and terrifying at the same time.

My art attempts to capture a moment of history, that is playful, referential to my practice yet still a meme. So I created this NFT as my first incorporation and introduction to the crypto space.

metadata.name: VeeCon 2022 #2827
metadata.description:
VeeCon 2022 - Created By Snowfro and Gary Vaynerchuk.

This token is a verifiable ticket for admission to VeeCon 2022, which is a multi-day event exclusively created for VeeFriends & the Web3 community.

Time: May 19th - May 22nd, 2022

Location: U.S. Bank Stadium in Minneapolis, MN, USA

To be admitted to VeeCon 2022, attendees must hold this token in a mobile-compatible NFT wallet and register it for admission with the official VeeCon event app. The VeeCon event and ticket registration app will be released in May 2022 on iOS and Android and will be used for verifiable ownership of this NFT, event registration, and programming.

To commemorate the first ever VeeCon conference, VeeFriends is honored to collaborate with Web 3 pioneer Erick 'Snowfro' Calderon. Snowfro, the founder of Art Blocks, a first of its kind generative blockchain platform, and creator of the Chromie Squiggle, collaborated on this collection during early Spring 2022 with Gary Vaynerchuk, the creator and visionary behind VeeFriends. Snowfro's squiqqles and Gary's doodles have melded together to create the artwork for the first NFT ticketed conference and to live forever on the ethereum blockchain.

If you plan to attend VeeCon 2022 with this ticket NFT please RSVP now at [VeeCon.co/RSVP](https://veecon.co/rsvp)

Instructions for how to use this ticket to gain admission to VeeCon are coming soon to [VeeCon.co](https://veecon.co/)!

My receipts evoke the iconic long receipt of a certain drug store chain, but they are screen printed, signed and numbered on rag paper. Classy and tangible.‚Äù 

Collectors who buy a NFT receive a screen printed (4‚Äùx23‚Äù) receipt. Collectors who buy all three NFT‚Äôs can trade in their three receipts for a 1/1 painting (dimensions, materials and delivery TBD by artist and collector, and service is my only product).

The NFT‚Äôs are thoughts, the receipts are the objects, and the painting is the action. You could have it all.

metadata.name: Stop Burning Art
metadata.description:
ED.150

.
First it's burning art, what's next? Burning books?

It's a dangerous slope, and do not try to do that only trying to flip a regular physical print as NFT with some media buzz. It will not make a ripple in art history dialogues, and even as art vandals, there are rules. 

Burning art is similar to going to a museum and slash some works done by others; you can try to discreetly hang your pieces on the wall and document the process that's ingenuity but not destroying others' works for your own benefit.

Use #StopBurningArt on social media and raise the dialogue. No one's physical art should be burnt. If you collect art, you have that trust and faith from the artists to protect the works well, not to destroy them.
